HEADWORD: Sea mouse
<hw>Sea" mouse`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A dorsibranchiate annelid, belonging to <gen>Aphrodite</gen> and
allied genera, having long, slender, hairlike setae on the sides.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The dunlin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

